{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"67264ab9-5f2c-4b99-9aec-7dadf0b1438e","content":"Analyzing .NET crash dumps is outside the scope of the available tools here (the `dump-collect` skill only covers *capturing* dumps, not analyzing them). However, here's how you can investigate your `.dmp` file:\n\n**Using `dotnet-dump analyze`** (cross-platform):\n```bash\ndotnet tool install -g dotnet-dump   # if not installed\ndotnet-dump analyze your-file.dmp\n```\nUseful SOS commands inside the analyzer:\n| Command | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `clrstack` | Managed call stack of crashing thread |\n| `pe` (PrintException) | Show last exception details |\n| `dumpheap -stat` | Heap summary (for OOM crashes) |\n| `threads` | List all managed threads |\n| `clrstack -all` | Stacks for all threads |\n\n**Using Visual Studio** (Windows):\n- Open the `.dmp` file directly → click **\"Debug with Managed Only\"**\n\n**Using `lldb` + SOS** (Linux/macOS):\n```bash\nlldb --core your-file.dmp\nplugin load /path/to/libsosplugin.so\nsos PrintException\n```\n\nA typical workflow: start with `pe` to check for an unhandled exception, then `clrstack` to see where it happened. Want help with any specific step?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"32e9e468-b2ee-4217-81f2-ade3fec9a76d","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about analyzing a .dmp crash dump file. Let me check the available skills - there's a \"dump-collect\" skill, but its description specifically says:\n\n- USE FOR: enabling automatic crash dumps, capturing dumps, setting up dump collection\n- DO NOT USE FOR: analyzing or debugging dumps, post-mortem investigation with lldb/windbg/dotnet-dump analyze\n\nSo the dump-collect skill is NOT appropriate here since the user wants to analyze a dump, not collect one.\n\nI should help the user directly with guidance on analyzing their crash dump.","outputTokens":462},"id":"b2f1935a-5a08-4baf-bf4f-0a238afb350a","timestamp":"2026-04-08T01:09:39.906Z","parentId":"f24ce6ac